ard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showPrevMessage?topicID=195.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showNextMessage?topicID=195.topic"> Next Topic >> </a> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95% cellpadding=5 cellspacing=1><tr><td valign=top background=http://www.graffe.com/home/bar_back.gif class=headings><font color=#FFFFFF>Author</font></td><td valign=top background=http://www.graffe.com/home/bar_back.gif class=headings><font color=#FFFFFF>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uienamarsuntaker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ienamar Suntaker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/1/01 3:44:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=195.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Just got 29, Quad Kiting Questions</span><hr size=1> I know what quad kiting is, and what the spell does, and all that; but where is a good place to practice this at 29?  And where is a good place to get xp with this at 29?  The two can be separate; i don't mind if i have to sacrifice some xp to practice well.  Please, share your titanic store of knowledge on this subject. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwandork.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wandor K</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/1/01 11:33:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=195.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Just got 29, Quad Kiting Questions</span><hr size=1> A good place to practice is the gobbie tower in Lake of Ill Omen. At 29 you will still be getting experience from them but they have relatively few hit points. Also, the zone to FM is not all that far if things go bad. Just be sure to have a SoW before you start - you won't make the zone with 4 mobs whacking you in the back. <p><div align="center" style="font-size: 12px; font-family: arial"><a target="_blank" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6103"><b>Wandor Kilbringer</b></a><br>Evoker of the 58th Conclave<br><span style="font-size: 10px">Vini, Vidi, Nuki</b><br><i>I came, I saw, I nuked the crap out of everything in sight!</i></span><p><b><a target="_blank" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6102 ">Moordian Kilbringer</a></b><br>Warrior of 33 Battle Scars</div></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaniar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aniar</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.docsmooth.com/images/dot.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/2/01 8:57:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=195.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.docsmooth.com/images/me.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Just got 29, Quad Kiting Questions</span><hr size=1> Goblin tower in LOIO I pull from for 1 blue bub XP / quad is north of the sarnak tower, west of the lake - there's ruins there with 4 goblins in one building - just run thru there, and they'll all pick you up.  Just make SURE you ahve your skin up.<br><br>use Bonds of Force to snare them, then use Column of Lightning to beat 'em down.<br><br>A few notes on Bonds of Force:  you can snare yourself - the only time that BoF will hit 5 targets is if you're the 5th.  Make sure you've got PLENTY of room before casting it.  A good way to judge this is to run till they're out of range, then cast it as soon as they get in range.  Learn this now, not the way I did.<br><br>BoF only lasts 2 minutes.  That's enough time to kill 'em, but don't screw around.  Get them dead, and go med up for the next quad.<br><br>Column of Lightning will hit 4 mobs + you if you're too close - stay out of range for that one, too. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>The goblins in the tower spawn slower than I can med from 20m to FOM, cast leatherskin, remed to full, cast tboots.  I run over to them, then, and wait for all 4 to spawn while invis.  Med along the lakeshore line to avoid skeletons while invis.<br><br>Good luck! <p><br>Aniar Orrenson<br>Wizard of the 30th Season<br>High Councilman of the Nightwatch of Norrath<br>"You look up overkill in the dictionary and there's a picture of Aniar lol" Lotta on Saryrn<br>Vigor says, 'warriors will hit anything wether its dead or alive.  they are stupid like that' </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaragoon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aragoon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/5/01 2:38:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=195.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Just got 29, Quad Kiting Questions</span><hr size=1> Very nice info, I have still 3 LvL to go. I just need those jboots or SOW potions. Where can i get booth of them and/or how much do they cost? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwandork.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wandor K</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/5/01 9:39:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=195.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Just got 29, Quad Kiting Questions</span><hr size=1> you can purchase SoW potions from your friendly local shaman. They usually go for 100pp for a 10 charge potion.<br><br>Forget Jboots for now - you will have to camp the Ancient Cyclops in SRo or OOT to get his ring for the quest. You won't be able to take the SRo one until mid 30s and the OOT one until mid 40s. Just buy SoW potions until you feel like you are up for a ridiculously long camp. <p><div align="center" style="font-size: 12px; font-family: arial"><a target="_blank" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6103"><b>Wandor Kilbringer</b></a><br>Evoker of the 58th Conclave<br><span style="font-size: 10px">Vini, Vidi, Nuki</b><br><i>I came, I saw, I nuked the crap out of everything in sight!</i></span><p><b><a target="_blank" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6102 ">Moordian Kilbringer</a></b><br>Warrior of 33 Battle Scars</div></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaniar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aniar</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.docsmooth.com/images/dot.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/5/01 11:03:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=195.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.docsmooth.com/images/me.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Just got 29, Quad Kiting Questions</span><hr size=1> Or get REALLY lucky and come up with about 5500kpp and buy tboots from the basement of Solusek's Eye (SolA) - that's what I did.  Mind you, getting 5500kpp at lvl 29 is TOUGH. <p><br>Aniar Orrenson<br>Wizard of the 31st Season<br>&lt;deguilded&gt;<br>"You look up overkill in the dictionary and there's a picture of Aniar lol" Lotta on Saryrn<br>Vigor says, 'warriors will hit anything wether its dead or alive.  they are stupid like that' </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugder.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gder</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/5/01 3:54:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=195.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Just got 29, Quad Kiting Questions</span><hr size=1> If your hunting in the Lake of Ill Manners I recomend stocking up on batwings.  They can be purchased from the top of the Wizard guild in Euriden and from an inn in East Commons.<br><br>When you need to med just levitate out over the lake, your perfectly safe from wanderers on the shore. <p><P></P><P>-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=</P><P>Gder of Mithanial Marr</P><P>aka</P><P>Master of his domain</P><P>aka</P><P>gder@gder.net</P></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaragoon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aragoon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/7/01 12:35:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=195.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Just got 29, Quad Kiting Questions</span><hr size=1> Thx for the help, I asked a friend about JBoots yesterday and he told me he would help me to get them. I have 270pp right now, an advisor Robe, polished bone bracs and some int rings in the bank. With those i can get the Money for the quest.<br><br>Do the Giants in EK drop the item at the same rate or are they harder to get of them because lower level? I just hope to get those boots before i am 34. Right now i am wearing leather boots from kerra island <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwandork.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wandor K</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/7/01 10:20:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=195.topic&index=8>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Just got 29, Quad Kiting Questions</span><hr size=1> the ring of the ancients you seek is only dropped by the Ancient Cyclops. He spawns in SRo and OOT. The OOT version is 10 levels higher. If you have a freind willing to help that is of high enough level, I would recommend OOT - its a single spawn camp with placeholders, much better than killing everything in sight in SRo.  <p><div align="center" style="font-size: 12px; font-family: arial"><a target="_blank" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6103"><b>Wandor Kilbringer</b></a><br>Evoker of the 58th Conclave<br><span style="font-size: 10px">Vini, Vidi, Nuki</b><br><i>I came, I saw, I nuked the crap out of everything in sight!</i></span><p><b><a target="_blank" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6102 ">Moordian Kilbringer</a></b><br>Warrior of 33 Battle Scars</div></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ufizzlebuster.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fizzlebuster</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/13/01 2:35:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=195.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.angelfire.com/games3/akumajfr/SHAG.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Just got 29, Quad Kiting Questions</span><hr size=1> I just made 29 as well, and had a couple questions...I'm gonna try those goblins as soon as I get a chance, but my question is...what do I do if one resists? Just run out of range, recast and then group them up and recast again to refresh? Seems like an awful lot of mana with CoL being so inefficient. I've got 205 int atm, but I don't want to run any risks.<br><br>Also, what happens when they try to run? Should BoF slow them down to stopping, or how should I finish them off? Thanks!<br><br>Fizzlebuster Grumpyfootball (grrr....)<br>29th Failed Experiment<br>Freeport Tavern Taxi of Morell Thule <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaniar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aniar</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.docsmooth.com/images/dot.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/15/01 8:47:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=195.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.docsmooth.com/images/me.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Just got 29, Quad Kiting Questions</span><hr size=1> If they &quot;run&quot; - BoF slows to the point they don't move.  it's kidna funny.  When I was 29, I didn't have the mana for multiple BoFs, so I'd run circles till BOF wore off, then try all 4 again full speed.  At 30, I had the mana to run straight, snare the resistor, cut back around and sit in the middle of all of 'em to regroup 'em, then resnare, then kite.<br><br>CoL inefficient?  against 1 maybe (135 mana / 137 dmg), but think that you're doing 4 of these...  135 mana / 548 dmg - a 4dmg : 1 mana ratio.  That's around 4500 dmg / kite at lvl 29.  Try telling ANYONE else that you can do 4500 dmg without getting hit OR running out of mana, and they won't believe you. heh. <p><br>Aniar Orrenson<br>Wizard of the 31st Season<br>Guild Leader of Nightwatch of Norrath<br>"You look up overkill in the dictionary and there's a picture of Aniar lol" Lotta on Saryrn<br>Vigor says, 'warriors will hit anything wether its dead or alive.  they are stupid like that' </p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showPrevMessage?topicID=195.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showNextMessage?topicID=195.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub23.ezb